AT|

I got a lot of varied responses. The only things the responses had in common were that none of them were equivocal and all lacked any discussion of standards that would be useful to my blog readers in the heat of battle. Almost everyone vilified hand one [hand on the left] as a perfect example of abuse and overuse of the 2 club opening bid. Hand 2 [right hand] gained more support and there was almost an even balance between 1 spade and 2 clubs.|
